result.execSummary:
Timothy R Johnson was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Timothy R Johnson was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Prosecutor Richard R. Lewis and Defendant, Timothy R Johnson, appeared in custody pro se.  Defendant to sign the waiver for extradition.    Defendant advised of right to an attorney. Waives the process of going through a formal extradition.    Defendant signed the waiver, and ADA Lewis and Deputy Pozombke signed the waiver as witnesses.
